<h1>Customizing applications</h1>
   
<p>Using EvoDico, customizing applications becomes quite easy and can be done while the application is running.</p>

<p>Simply click the "Customize" button on the right of the toolbar.</p>

<p><img alt="" src="pix/evoDico/customize_button.gif" class="shadow"  style="margin-left: 40px" /></p>

<p>Icons then appear near each UI element of the running application. Clicking these icons pops-up 
the corresponding designer page ready for changes.</p>

<div style="margin-left: 40px">
<p><img alt="" src="pix/evoDico/appDes.gif" class="shadow" /></p>

<p><img alt="" src="pix/evoDico/customize_fields.gif" class="shadow" /></p>

<p><img alt="" src="pix/evoDico/customize_fieldssearch.gif" class="shadow" /></p>
</div>
<p>The application page need to be re-loaded (simply by clicking the browser "refresh" button) for the changes to take effect.</p>

